"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-03-paris-olympics-2024-sports-minister-commends-two-nigerians-for-advancing-to-100m-semi-final\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Published on By The Honourable Minister of Sports Development, John Enoh, has commended the duo of Kanyinsola Ajayi and Favour Ashe for their remarkable performances in their respective heats, which ensured Nigeria remains represented in the men's 100m event at the ongoing 2024 Olympic Games in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 66, \"end\": 75, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Owan_Enoh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"John Enoh\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Owan_Enoh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Owan_Enoh\"}, {\"begin\": 210, \"end\": 217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999102610713, \"rank\": 8.945276420105799e-08, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}, {\"begin\": 299, \"end\": 304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999529172794, \"rank\": 4.7082733646048185e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Honourable Minister\", \"from\": 16, \"to\": 39}, {\"ngram\": \"Sports Development\", \"from\": 43, \"to\": 61}, {\"ngram\": \"the duo\", \"from\": 88, \"to\": 95}, {\"ngram\": \"Kanyinsola Ajayi\", \"from\": 99, \"to\": 115}, {\"ngram\": \"Favour Ashe\", \"from\": 120, \"to\": 131}, {\"ngram\": \"their remarkable performances\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 165}, {\"ngram\": \"their respective heats\", \"from\": 169, \"to\": 191}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's 100m\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 252}, {\"ngram\": \"event\", \"from\": 253, \"to\": 258}, {\"ngram\": \"the ongoing 2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 292}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was disclosed in a statement signed by Diana-Mary Nsan, S.A. Media to the Minister of Sports Development, on Saturday.\", \"from\": 307, \"to\": 430, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 329, \"to\": 340}, {\"ngram\": \"Diana-Mary Nsan\", \"from\": 351, \"to\": 366}, {\"ngram\": \"S.A. Media\", \"from\": 368, \"to\": 378}, {\"ngram\": \"the Minister\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 394}, {\"ngram\": \"Sports Development\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 416}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 421, \"to\": 429}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Saturday morning, national champion, Ajayi delivered a standout performance in heat 5, surprising many by defeating reigning Olympic Champion Marcell Jacobs with a winning time of 10.02 seconds.\", \"from\": 432, \"to\": 629, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Saturday morning\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 451}, {\"ngram\": \"national champion\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 470}, {\"ngram\": \"Ajayi\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 477}, {\"ngram\": \"a standout performance\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 510}, {\"ngram\": \"heat\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 518}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic Champion Marcell Jacobs\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 591}, {\"ngram\": \"a winning time\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 611}, {\"ngram\": \"10.02 seconds\", \"from\": 615, \"to\": 628}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jacobs followed closely with 10.05 seconds, and Abdul Rasheed Saminu finished third in 10.06 seconds.\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 732, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jacobs\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 637}, {\"ngram\": \"10.05 seconds\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 673}, {\"ngram\": \"Abdul Rasheed Saminu\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 699}, {\"ngram\": \"10.06 seconds\", \"from\": 718, \"to\": 731}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ashe, meanwhile, also made it to the semifinals, securing one of the fastest non-automatic qualifying spots.\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 842, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the semifinals\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 781}, {\"ngram\": \"the fastest non-automatic qualifying spots\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 841}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He placed fourth in heat 4 with a time of 10.16 seconds, following Oblique Seville (9.99s), Hakim Sani Brown (10.02s), and Puripol Boonson (10.13s).\", \"from\": 844, \"to\": 992, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 919, \"end\": 926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seville\", \"score\": 0.9999997838436008, \"rank\": 1.1600307617067013e-07, \"text\": \"Seville\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seville\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seville\"}, {\"begin\": 936, \"end\": 941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_of_Bahrain\", \"score\": 0.5639361577296105, \"rank\": 0.6693961838964068, \"text\": \"Hakim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_of_Bahrain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_of_Bahrain\"}, {\"begin\": 942, \"end\": 946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shani\", \"score\": 0.999999945317542, \"rank\": 5.4671109294731386e-08, \"text\": \"Sani\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shani\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"heat\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 868}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 882}, {\"ngram\": \"10.16 seconds\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 899}, {\"ngram\": \"(9.99s\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 933}, {\"ngram\": \"(10.02s\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 960}, {\"ngram\": \"Puripol Boonson\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 982}, {\"ngram\": \"10.13s\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 990}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Enoh commended both athletes for rising to the challenge and charged them to aim for further success as the semifinals and final take place tomorrow evening.\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1151, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Enoh\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 998}, {\"ngram\": \"both athletes\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1022}, {\"ngram\": \"the challenge\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1050}, {\"ngram\": \"further success\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1094}, {\"ngram\": \"the semifinals\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1112}, {\"ngram\": \"final take place\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1133}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He emphasized the importance of maintaining resilience and focus as they compete on the global stage.\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1254, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the importance\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1181}, {\"ngram\": \"resilience\", \"from\": 1197, \"to\": 1207}, {\"ngram\": \"the global stage\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1253}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also, Team Nigeria's 16-year-old swimmer Adaku Nwandu narrowly missed out on qualifying for the Women's 50m Freestyle final.\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1267, \"end\": 1274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999102610713, \"rank\": 8.945276420105799e-08, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Adaku Nwandu\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1309}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She finished second in her heat with a time of 26.62 seconds but did not rank among the 16 fastest times needed to advance.\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1505, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her heat\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1413}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1425}, {\"ngram\": \"26.62 seconds\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1442}, {\"ngram\": \"the 16 fastest times\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1486}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Enoh congratulated Nwandu on her fine performance in Paris and expressed confidence in her potential for future achievements.\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1632, \"entities\": [{